news.title: UK's Land Securities sells '21 Moorfields' property to Lendlease for $917 million
news.para: A 568,500 square feet property, 21 Moorfields was fully pre-let to Deutsche Bank on a 25-year lease for housing the German firm's London headquarters.

news.title: SoftBank said to cut valuation of IPO-bound Oyo to $2.7 billion
news.para: ​Oyo, formally known as Oravel Stays Ltd., filed a fresh round of financial documents with India’s market regulator on Monday as it plans for a stock-market debut after cost cuts and recovery in travel helped it reduce losses.

news.title: Birla Estates buys 10 acre land in Bengaluru for housing project
news.para: ​Birla Estates Pvt Ltd, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Century Textiles and Industries Ltd, said in a statement that it has acquired a 10-acre land parcel at Raja Rajeshwari Nagar, South Bengaluru.

news.title: Hong Kong's finance chief says no sharp risk to property prices
news.para: Finance Secretary Paul Chan was speaking after the Hong Kong Monetary Authority raised its base rate charged through the overnight discount window by 75 basis points to 3.5%, its highest since October 2008, following the same move by the U.S. Federal Reserve.

news.title: NCRTC to develop serviced apartments in Delhi's Jungpura
news.para: The corporation plans to develop 149 one-bedroom units at the site and use the income generated from the serviced apartments to smoothen the operation of the RRTS trains, people in the know said.

news.title: Assam government to hire third party to collect property tax from four towns
news.para: The state government in a statement on Wednesday said this move to engage a third party is a step towards the financial empowerment of urban local bodies in the state and is at no additional cost to the municipal bodies and “shall not enhance the existing tax rates to the citizens”.

news.title: Delhi development authority to notify master plan by April 2023
news.para: The DDA told the apex court that the tentative date for placing the Master Plan for Delhi (MPD-2041) before the authorities is the first week of December, 2022, and, if any, would be made by the last week of December, 2022.

news.title: Odisha government rolls out digital land registry services
news.para: ​​The partnership aims to enhance the land and property transaction process for people by improving the current computerized e-registration services offered at 191 registration offices across the state, said official sources.

news.title: Nearly 5% of Chandigarh housing board small flats illegally occupied: Survey
news.para: According to the survey, 1,268 (7%) were found locked and in 130 cases, the occupants denied to give any information to the CHB officials, 211 were with the government departments, three were found vacant and four sealed by CHB.

news.title: Rent control court to get operational in Nashik
news.para: The Rent Control Act court in Nashik would restart functioning after a gap of around two years. President of Nashik Bar Association Nitin Thakre said they had also filed a writ petition in the Bombay high court on this issue.

news.title: LG steps in, Delhi development authority sells 870 Narela flats in 15 days
news.para: DDA has been offering 509 LIG and 772 EWS flats at Narela on a first come, first served basis from September 5, for which it has received 1,940 registrations and 870 flats — 619 EWS and 251 LIG flats — have already been sold.

news.title: Hit by power blow, Lavasa residents seek Maharashtra CM's help
news.para: With Rs22.78 crore dues pending with the Lavasa Corporation Limited, MSEDCL started disconnecting power to the water supply stations, sewage treatment plants, street lights and the main town hall in the privately planned hill city from last week.

news.title: Home buyers, RWAs in dilemma over repairs after Bengaluru flood
news.para: Real estate experts feel that due to ambiguity in the property laws, and a lack of awareness about property laws is forcing buyers to pay for maintenance even though the ownership of the common areas lies with the builder as the apartment associations are not legally registered and the land is not conveyed to the association.

news.title: Cracks visible in Chintels Paradiso balconies: Gurugram DC after visit
news.para: After the visit, the DC said a decision on these two towers will be taken only after the IIT-D submits its report on the structural safety of the Sector 109 society's tower D, where a vertical collapse of five living room floors left two residents dead earlier this year.

news.title: Avendus Capital leases 1 lakh sq ft in Mumbai's BKC
news.para: The company will be paying average monthly rentals of Rs 278 per sq ft including the rental escalation over the total tenure of the lease, taking its total pay out to around Rs 153.44 crore during the entire term.
